    <stitle>Body Builder Electrical Data Book - SINGLE REDUCTION AXLES: SPICER S100-S, S105-S, S135-S, S150-S -
        LUBRICATION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>LUBRICATION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>To ensure proper lubrication and operating temperature, correct lubricants and lubricant levels must
                be maintained. Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICANTS AND SEALERS in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Lubricant close enough to bottom of opening to be seen or touched is not sufficient. Lubricant
                        must be level with opening (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1401733">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1401733" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401733" filename="../figg14/G1401733.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="208px"
                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Lubricant Must Be Level With Opening</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
    </svcsubsec>
